display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> is strictly compatible with the filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>;
        in other words, the spectral sequence defined by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1=E_\infty ]]></fr:tex>) <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2"
href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="1.3.2" />.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

